The use of iterative search algorithms and convergence analysis suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The discussion of data-generating processes and estimation methods suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.IT (Information Theory). The focus on causal relations and network structures suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.ST (Statistics). Finally, the use of non-Gaussianity and causal ordering suggests a potential fit with the sub-category of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
